<h2 id="step-9-use-emphasis">Step 9: Use emphasis</h2>

<p>Let‚Äôs try something new. You can use bold and italic text in Markdown. There are a couple of ways to create emphasis.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-md" data-lang="md">  <span class="ge">*This text will be italic*</span>
  _This will also be italic_

  <span class="gs">**This text will be bold**</span>
  __This will also be bold__

  _You <span class="gs">**can**</span> combine them_

  </code></pre></figure>

<h4 id="activity-add-some-emphasis">Activity: Add some emphasis</h4>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Edit the file <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">_includes/05-emphasis.md</code> in this pull request.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Use the Preview tab and your ‚ú® new Markdown knowledge, add emphasis (like bold or italics) to your skills.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Commit your changes.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

